00:52:16.699 --> 00:52:28.190
To encourage us to promptly follow-up on interest

00:52:28.190 --> 00:52:30.190
that we find in the Phil ministry,

00:52:30.190 --> 00:52:36.190
Paul Likens our work to a plant that grows from a little seed.

00:52:36.190 --> 00:52:41.190
Now, what vital for a planted seed to grow?

00:52:41.190 --> 00:52:43.190
One authority says,

00:52:43.190 --> 00:52:47.190
of all the factors that determine seed germination,

00:52:47.190 --> 00:52:51.190
water is the first and most important.

00:52:51.190 --> 00:52:53.190
And another reference says,

00:52:53.190 --> 00:52:55.190
until seeds have sprouted,

00:52:55.190 --> 00:52:58.190
keep the seed bed moist,

00:52:58.190 --> 00:53:01.190
never allowing it to dry out.

00:53:01.190 --> 00:53:06.190
So, what will happen to a seed that is not watered?

00:53:06.190 --> 00:53:08.190
Nothing.

00:53:08.190 --> 00:53:10.190
It will lay dormant.

00:53:10.190 --> 00:53:14.190
The regular watering is vital for a seed to sprout,

00:53:14.190 --> 00:53:16.190
to take root,

00:53:16.190 --> 00:53:19.190
and in fact continue to grow.

00:53:19.190 --> 00:53:21.190
Now, with these facts in mind,

00:53:21.190 --> 00:53:25.190
Paul's words at 1 Corinthians 3 and verse 6

00:53:25.190 --> 00:53:28.190
shows that more is required

00:53:28.190 --> 00:53:31.190
than simply planting a seed of truth.

00:53:31.190 --> 00:53:33.190
Let's note his words.

00:53:33.190 --> 00:53:38.190
It's in 1 Corinthians 3 and verse 6.

00:53:38.190 --> 00:53:41.079
It says,

00:53:41.079 --> 00:53:44.079
I planted Apollo's watered,

00:53:44.079 --> 00:53:47.079
but God kept making it grow.

00:53:47.079 --> 00:53:50.079
Though all credit goes to Jehovah God

00:53:50.079 --> 00:53:52.079
for making the spiritual seed grow,

00:53:52.079 --> 00:53:56.079
but he allows us to have a role in the process.

00:53:56.079 --> 00:54:01.079
Did you notice the important role Apollo's played?

00:54:01.079 --> 00:54:03.079
He did the watering.

00:54:03.079 --> 00:54:05.079
In a regular way,

00:54:05.079 --> 00:54:08.079
he helped keep the spiritual soil

00:54:08.079 --> 00:54:10.079
of the individual moist,

00:54:10.079 --> 00:54:13.079
never allowing it to dry out.

00:54:13.079 --> 00:54:15.079
Many people who show interest

00:54:15.079 --> 00:54:17.079
in the Kingdom message today

00:54:17.079 --> 00:54:21.079
are searching for their truth about God.

00:54:21.079 --> 00:54:24.079
In order to teach them progressively,

00:54:24.079 --> 00:54:28.079
we must return again and again.

00:54:28.079 --> 00:54:31.079
This requires good preparation

00:54:31.079 --> 00:54:35.079
and organization on our part.

00:54:35.079 --> 00:54:38.079
By promptly making return visits,

00:54:38.079 --> 00:54:42.079
we demonstrate a sincere concern for the individual,

00:54:42.079 --> 00:54:45.079
wanting to help them grow spiritually

00:54:45.079 --> 00:54:49.079
and develop a relationship with Jehovah.

