that is the fruit of our lips

01:14:51.300 --> 01:14:55.300
that make public declaration to His name.

01:14:55.300 --> 01:14:58.300
Moreover, do not forget to do good

01:14:58.300 --> 01:15:01.300
and to share what you have with others.

01:15:01.300 --> 01:15:07.300
For God is well pleased with such sacrifices.

01:15:07.300 --> 01:15:10.300
Your readiness to share the good news of peace

01:15:10.300 --> 01:15:14.300
with others is just such a sacrifice.

01:15:14.300 --> 01:15:19.300
And you can rest assured that Jehovah is thoroughly pleased

01:15:19.300 --> 01:15:25.640
with your loving and faithful service to Him.

01:15:25.640 --> 01:15:28.640
Thank you, brothers, for helping us to be ready

01:15:28.640 --> 01:15:31.640
to share the good news of peace effectively

01:15:31.640 --> 01:15:35.560
at every opportunity.

01:15:35.560 --> 01:15:38.560
Jehovah's organization continues to grow

01:15:38.560 --> 01:15:41.560
and there is plenty of work to do.

01:15:41.560 --> 01:15:44.560
Young people in particular have many opportunities

01:15:44.560 --> 01:15:47.560
to expand their service.

01:15:47.560 --> 01:15:49.560
How can a career in full-time service

01:15:49.560 --> 01:15:53.560
lead to rich blessings now and in the future?

01:15:53.560 --> 01:15:58.560
What are some common obstacles to pursuing full-time service?

01:15:58.560 --> 01:16:01.560
How can they be overcome?

01:16:01.560 --> 01:16:04.560
We encourage young ones to give special attention

01:16:04.560 --> 01:16:06.560
to the next talk.

01:16:06.560 --> 01:16:08.560
For the Mark Sanderson,

01:16:08.560 --> 01:16:12.560
a member of the governing body will develop the theme,

01:16:12.560 --> 01:16:17.560
young people, choose a path that leads to peace.

01:16:17.560 --> 01:16:28.500
An 18-year-old brother was trying to decide

01:16:28.500 --> 01:16:31.500
what he wanted to do after high school.

01:16:31.500 --> 01:16:33.500
He was raised in the truth.

01:16:33.500 --> 01:16:37.500
And in his heart, he wanted to be a pioneer.

01:16:37.500 --> 01:16:41.500
But he also had a scholarship to go to university

01:16:41.500 --> 01:16:43.500
and some other grants.

01:16:43.500 --> 01:16:45.500
And he had been accepted to attend.

01:16:45.500 --> 01:16:47.500
He had many questions.

01:16:47.500 --> 01:16:50.500
How was he going to support himself

01:16:50.500 --> 01:16:53.500
and much pressure from his teachers and counselors

01:16:53.500 --> 01:16:56.500
to go to university?

01:16:56.500 --> 01:16:59.500
What decision would he make?

01:16:59.500 --> 01:17:01.500
Well, maybe many of you young ones

01:17:01.500 --> 01:17:03.500
who are listening to this talk right now

01:17:03.500 --> 01:17:06.500
are facing that same decision.

01:17:06.500 --> 01:17:10.500
Or maybe you will be in a year or two.

01:17:10.500 --> 01:17:13.500
What path will you take?

01:17:13.500 --> 01:17:16.500
Well, now here's what we know.

01:17:16.500 --> 01:17:20.500
Jehovah wants you to have not just a good life,

01:17:20.500 --> 01:17:22.500
not just an average life.

01:17:22.500 --> 01:17:26.500
He wants you to have an awesome, wonderful life,

01:17:26.500 --> 01:17:29.500
both now during your youth,

01:17:29.500 --> 01:17:33.500
but really for your entire life.

01:17:33.500 --> 01:17:36.500
That's why the Bible says in Ecclesiastes,

01:17:36.500 --> 01:17:40.500
chapter 11 and verse 9,

01:17:40.500 --> 01:17:44.500
rejoice young man while you were young.

01:17:44.500 --> 01:17:47.500
And let your heart be glad

01:17:47.500 --> 01:17:49.500
in the days of your youth.

01:17:49.500 --> 01:17:53.500
Well, many young people have found real joy

01:17:53.500 --> 01:17:57.500
and peace by choosing a career

01:17:57.500 --> 01:17:59.500
in the full-time service.

01:17:59.500 --> 01:18:01.500
But now, when we say full-time service,

01:18:01.500 --> 01:18:03.500
what are we talking about?

01:18:03.500 --> 01:18:06.500
Well, full-time service is not just one thing.

01:18:06.500 --> 01:18:09.500
It actually includes many things.

01:18:09.500 --> 01:18:13.500
It includes pioneering maybe in your home congregation

01:18:13.500 --> 01:18:15.500
or maybe in another area,

01:18:15.500 --> 01:18:18.500
maybe in another city, state, province,

01:18:18.500 --> 01:18:20.500
even in another country.

01:18:20.500 --> 01:18:22.500
It might mean assisting with

01:18:22.500 --> 01:18:24.500
theocratic construction projects,

01:18:24.500 --> 01:18:27.500
maybe building kingdom halls or assembly halls

01:18:27.500 --> 01:18:30.500
or building remote translation offices

01:18:30.500 --> 01:18:34.500
or even working at Bethel facilities.

01:18:34.500 --> 01:18:36.500
And it also could mean submitting an application

01:18:36.500 --> 01:18:40.500
for Bethel service and becoming a Bethelite.

01:18:40.500 --> 01:18:45.500
Really, there are so many wonderful opportunities

01:18:45.500 --> 01:18:48.500
that are available for you young ones

01:18:48.500 --> 01:18:51.500
in full-time service.

01:18:51.500 --> 01:18:53.500
But now, here's a question.

01:18:53.500 --> 01:18:56.500
What challenges could prevent you

01:18:56.500 --> 01:18:59.500
from starting or continuing

01:18:59.500 --> 01:19:01.500
on the path of full-time service?

01:19:01.500 --> 01:19:03.500
And more importantly,

01:19:03.500 --> 01:19:07.500
how can you overcome those challenges?

01:19:07.500 --> 01:19:11.500
Well, let's talk about three obstacles.

01:19:11.500 --> 01:19:13.500
Here's the first one.

01:19:13.500 --> 01:19:15.500
It's financial concerns.

01:19:15.500 --> 01:19:18.500
How am I going to support myself?

01:19:18.500 --> 01:19:21.500
Well, let's look at something that Jesus said.

01:19:21.500 --> 01:19:24.500
In Matthew, chapter 6,

01:19:24.500 --> 01:19:29.800
and verse 33,

01:19:29.800 --> 01:19:32.800
Matthew 6, verse 33, Jesus said,

01:19:32.800 --> 01:19:35.800
keep on then seeking first the kingdom

01:19:35.800 --> 01:19:37.800
and his righteousness,

01:19:37.800 --> 01:19:40.800
and all these other things

01:19:40.800 --> 01:19:42.800
will be added to you.

01:19:42.800 --> 01:19:44.800
Well, now, okay.

01:19:44.800 --> 01:19:47.800
It says all these other things,

01:19:47.800 --> 01:19:48.800
what other things?

01:19:48.800 --> 01:19:51.800
What is Jesus talking about here?

01:19:51.800 --> 01:19:52.800
Well, to find out,

01:19:52.800 --> 01:19:55.800
when do we go back up to verse 25?

01:19:55.800 --> 01:19:57.800
And let's read a little bit more

01:19:57.800 --> 01:19:59.800
of what Jesus was talking about

01:19:59.800 --> 01:20:01.800
when he said those famous words.

01:20:01.800 --> 01:20:02.800
Verse 25,

01:20:02.800 --> 01:20:04.800
on this account,

01:20:04.800 --> 01:20:05.800
I say to you,

01:20:05.800 --> 01:20:08.800
stop being anxious about your lives

01:20:08.800 --> 01:20:10.800
as to what you will eat

01:20:10.800 --> 01:20:12.800
or what you will drink

01:20:12.800 --> 01:20:14.800
or about your bodies

01:20:14.800 --> 01:20:16.800
as to what you will wear.

01:20:16.800 --> 01:20:18.800
Does not life mean more than food

01:20:18.800 --> 01:20:20.800
and the body than clothing?

01:20:20.800 --> 01:20:22.800
Now, after identifying,

01:20:22.800 --> 01:20:24.800
now we know what Jesus is talking about.

01:20:24.800 --> 01:20:26.800
He's talking about our necessities,

01:20:26.800 --> 01:20:28.800
food, shelter, clothing.

01:20:28.800 --> 01:20:30.800
But now, look at the illustrations

01:20:30.800 --> 01:20:32.800
Jesus goes on to give now,

01:20:32.800 --> 01:20:34.800
beginning here in verse 26.

01:20:34.800 --> 01:20:36.800
Observe intently

01:20:36.800 --> 01:20:38.800
the birds of heaven.

01:20:38.800 --> 01:20:40.800
They do not so seed

01:20:40.800 --> 01:20:41.800
or reap

01:20:41.800 --> 01:20:43.800
or gather into storehouses

01:20:43.800 --> 01:20:46.800
yet your heavenly Father feeds them.

01:20:46.800 --> 01:20:49.800
Are you not worth more than they are?

01:20:50.800 --> 01:20:52.800
Who of you by being anxious

01:20:52.800 --> 01:20:55.800
can add one qubit to his life's man?

01:20:55.800 --> 01:20:58.800
Also, why are you anxious about clothing?

01:20:58.800 --> 01:21:01.800
Take a lesson from the lilies of the field,

01:21:01.800 --> 01:21:02.800
how they grow,

01:21:02.800 --> 01:21:04.800
they do not toil,

01:21:04.800 --> 01:21:05.800
nor do they spin.

01:21:05.800 --> 01:21:08.800
But I tell you that not even Solomon

01:21:08.800 --> 01:21:10.800
in all his glory

01:21:10.800 --> 01:21:12.800
was arrayed as one of these.

01:21:12.800 --> 01:21:14.800
Now, if this is how God clothes

01:21:14.800 --> 01:21:16.800
the vegetation of the field

01:21:16.800 --> 01:21:17.800
that's here today

01:21:17.800 --> 01:21:20.800
and tomorrow is thrown into the oven,

01:21:20.800 --> 01:21:22.800
will he not much rather clothes

01:21:22.800 --> 01:21:25.800
you, you with little faith?

01:21:25.800 --> 01:21:27.800
So, never be anxious

01:21:27.800 --> 01:21:29.800
and say, what are we to eat

01:21:29.800 --> 01:21:30.800
or what are we to drink

01:21:30.800 --> 01:21:32.800
or what are we to wear?

01:21:32.800 --> 01:21:33.800
For all these are the things

01:21:33.800 --> 01:21:35.800
the nations are eagerly pursuing.

01:21:35.800 --> 01:21:38.800
Your heavenly Father knows

01:21:38.800 --> 01:21:41.800
that you need all these things.

01:21:41.800 --> 01:21:44.800
Well, do you get the sense of this?

01:21:44.800 --> 01:21:47.800
Jesus was trying to reason

01:21:47.800 --> 01:21:49.800
that just as Jehovah provides

01:21:49.800 --> 01:21:51.800
for all of his creation,

01:21:51.800 --> 01:21:54.800
he can provide for you too.

01:21:54.800 --> 01:21:57.800
We just need to develop our faith

01:21:57.800 --> 01:21:59.800
that Jehovah will provide

01:21:59.800 --> 01:22:01.800
the things we need

01:22:01.800 --> 01:22:04.800
if we put his service first.

01:22:04.800 --> 01:22:06.800
Well, does that mean

01:22:06.800 --> 01:22:07.800
that Jehovah is just going to drop

01:22:07.800 --> 01:22:08.800
into our lap

01:22:08.800 --> 01:22:10.800
everything that we need?

01:22:10.800 --> 01:22:11.800
Well, no.

01:22:11.800 --> 01:22:14.800
Jehovah expects that we're going to use

01:22:14.800 --> 01:22:16.800
the things that he's given us

01:22:16.800 --> 01:22:18.800
to be able to support ourselves.

01:22:18.800 --> 01:22:20.800
So, it's very wise,

01:22:20.800 --> 01:22:21.800
when you're young,

01:22:21.800 --> 01:22:23.800
to plan ahead

01:22:23.800 --> 01:22:25.800
so that you can obtain the skills

01:22:25.800 --> 01:22:28.800
you need to be able to support yourself.

01:22:28.800 --> 01:22:30.800
Now, in some lands,

01:22:30.800 --> 01:22:33.800
it may be that as you're growing up,

01:22:33.800 --> 01:22:34.800
you can learn a trade

01:22:34.800 --> 01:22:35.800
from your Father

01:22:35.800 --> 01:22:36.800
or from your mother

01:22:36.800 --> 01:22:39.800
or maybe even from another relative.

01:22:39.800 --> 01:22:42.800
In other lands, you might be able

01:22:42.800 --> 01:22:43.800
while you're still in high school

01:22:43.800 --> 01:22:45.800
to take some vocational courses

01:22:45.800 --> 01:22:48.800
that would help you to learn a skill

01:22:48.800 --> 01:22:50.800
or learn a trade.

01:22:50.800 --> 01:22:52.800
But here's the point.

01:22:52.800 --> 01:22:54.800
We need to plan.

01:22:54.800 --> 01:22:56.800
So, ask yourself,

01:22:56.800 --> 01:22:58.800
what abilities and skills do I have

01:22:58.800 --> 01:23:01.800
that I could use to support myself?

01:23:01.800 --> 01:23:03.800
A sister named Kelly

01:23:03.800 --> 01:23:05.800
had a very clear goal in mind

01:23:05.800 --> 01:23:06.800
of becoming a pioneer.

01:23:06.800 --> 01:23:08.800
So, what did she do?

01:23:08.800 --> 01:23:10.800
Well, this is what she says.

01:23:10.800 --> 01:23:11.800
I had to choose something

01:23:11.800 --> 01:23:13.800
that would allow me to support myself

01:23:13.800 --> 01:23:15.800
in my ministry.

01:23:15.800 --> 01:23:18.800
Kelly enrolled in a vocational program

01:23:18.800 --> 01:23:19.800
in her high school.

01:23:19.800 --> 01:23:21.800
And that helped her to achieve

01:23:21.800 --> 01:23:22.800
her primary goal.

01:23:22.800 --> 01:23:24.800
Here's what she said.

01:23:24.800 --> 01:23:26.800
The full-time ministry

01:23:26.800 --> 01:23:28.800
was what I wanted to do.

01:23:28.800 --> 01:23:32.800
Everything else was secondary.

01:23:32.800 --> 01:23:34.800
Well, how does Kelly feel now

01:23:34.800 --> 01:23:36.800
about the decision that she made?

01:23:36.800 --> 01:23:38.800
She says, I feel my decision

01:23:38.800 --> 01:23:42.800
was the best one that I could have made.

01:23:42.800 --> 01:23:44.800
You, young brothers and sisters,

01:23:44.800 --> 01:23:46.800
you can overcome that challenge

01:23:46.800 --> 01:23:48.800
just by planning ahead

01:23:48.800 --> 01:23:51.800
and making sure that you have practical skills

01:23:51.800 --> 01:23:54.800
you can use to support yourself.

01:23:54.800 --> 01:23:57.800
Here's the second obstacle.

01:23:57.800 --> 01:23:59.800
Pressure from others.

01:23:59.800 --> 01:24:03.800
My relatives want me to focus on making money.

01:24:03.800 --> 01:24:05.800
Well, if that's the case,

01:24:05.800 --> 01:24:08.800
explain your spiritual goals

01:24:08.800 --> 01:24:11.800
in a calm, respectful way.

01:24:11.800 --> 01:24:14.800
Colossians chapter four in verse six says,

01:24:14.800 --> 01:24:18.800
let your words always be gracious,

01:24:18.800 --> 01:24:20.800
seasoned with salt.

01:24:20.800 --> 01:24:21.800
Well, we all know

01:24:21.800 --> 01:24:23.800
when we eat food with no salt

01:24:23.800 --> 01:24:25.800
doesn't taste very good, does it?

01:24:25.800 --> 01:24:27.800
You put a little salt on it,

01:24:27.800 --> 01:24:29.800
now it becomes delicious.

01:24:29.800 --> 01:24:32.800
So, make sure that when you speak

01:24:32.800 --> 01:24:33.800
to your relatives,

01:24:33.800 --> 01:24:36.800
you put a little salt on those words

01:24:36.800 --> 01:24:38.800
so that you can reason with them

01:24:38.800 --> 01:24:40.800
and help them to see the wisdom

01:24:40.800 --> 01:24:43.800
of the decision that you want to make.

01:24:43.800 --> 01:24:45.800
Well, it could be your relatives

01:24:45.800 --> 01:24:47.800
will not agree with you.

01:24:47.800 --> 01:24:50.800
But let's look at something that Jesus said here at Luke,

01:24:50.800 --> 01:24:52.800
chapter seven,

01:24:52.800 --> 01:24:54.800
and verse 35,

01:24:54.800 --> 01:24:59.590
Jesus said all the same.

01:24:59.590 --> 01:25:01.590
Wisdom is proved righteous,

01:25:01.590 --> 01:25:03.590
or now if you look at the footnote,

01:25:03.590 --> 01:25:06.590
it says, or is vindicated

01:25:06.590 --> 01:25:09.590
by all its children.

01:25:09.590 --> 01:25:11.590
Well, now what's the point?

01:25:11.590 --> 01:25:14.590
Well, sometimes when people make a decision,

01:25:14.590 --> 01:25:17.590
we're not sure if it was the right one or not.

01:25:17.590 --> 01:25:20.590
But when the decision works out well,

01:25:20.590 --> 01:25:22.590
when it leads to success,

01:25:22.590 --> 01:25:25.590
when people see how happy you are

01:25:25.590 --> 01:25:27.590
and how successful you are,

01:25:27.590 --> 01:25:29.590
the joy, the satisfaction you have,

01:25:29.590 --> 01:25:31.590
well, then what happens?

01:25:31.590 --> 01:25:33.590
Well, maybe your relatives will see

01:25:33.590 --> 01:25:36.590
that your decision has been vindicated.

01:25:36.590 --> 01:25:38.590
It's been proved righteous

01:25:38.590 --> 01:25:41.590
by the way things have turned out.

01:25:41.590 --> 01:25:44.590
Here's obstacle number three.

01:25:44.590 --> 01:25:46.590
Unexpected challenges.

01:25:46.590 --> 01:25:50.590
I thought it was going to be easier than this.

01:25:50.590 --> 01:25:54.590
Well, those unexpected challenges can be many.

01:25:54.590 --> 01:25:58.590
It could be just trying to get used to new roommates,

01:25:58.590 --> 01:26:01.590
dealing with personality challenges,

01:26:01.590 --> 01:26:04.590
or even just coping with homesickness.

01:26:04.590 --> 01:26:05.590
Here's the point.

01:26:05.590 --> 01:26:08.590
Don't give up.

01:26:08.590 --> 01:26:12.590
Notice what James said here in James chapter one,

01:26:12.590 --> 01:26:16.840
James chapter one,

01:26:16.840 --> 01:26:18.840
and verse four.

01:26:18.840 --> 01:26:21.840
Now, you notice, as you look at verse two,

01:26:21.840 --> 01:26:24.840
James is talking about trials,

01:26:24.840 --> 01:26:26.840
and he's talking about how trials

01:26:26.840 --> 01:26:28.840
can have a positive effect on us,

01:26:28.840 --> 01:26:31.840
but now look what he says in verse four.

01:26:31.840 --> 01:26:35.840
But let endurance complete its work

01:26:35.840 --> 01:26:38.840
so that you may be complete and sound

01:26:38.840 --> 01:26:43.840
in all respects, not lacking in anything.

01:26:43.840 --> 01:26:45.840
What's James trying to say?

01:26:45.840 --> 01:26:47.840
What's his point?

01:26:47.840 --> 01:26:49.840
Well, have you ever heard the expression,

01:26:49.840 --> 01:26:52.840
no pain, no gain?

01:26:52.840 --> 01:26:55.840
